  <summary date="2020-04-07T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">COVID&#8211;19 Price Gouging Prevention Act

This bill makes it unlawful for any person to sell or offer for sale a consumer good or service during a public health emergency resulting from COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) at a price that (1) is unconscionably excessive, and (2) indicates&#160;that the seller is using the circumstances related to&#160;the public health emergency to increase prices unreasonably.</summary>
